1 On gesceape ðonne ðære hwite rosan
2 me se æteowde ðæt halige werod
3 ðe on his blode Crist geworhte brýd;

34 geseonde Rome and hire heardan weorc,
35 forwundrode wæron, ða Lateranum
36 ofer ða deadlican ðing adan wæs;

64 And "Hwær is heo?", sodenlice cwæð ic.
65 And he: "To gefyllan ðinne willan,
66 Beatrijs me afyrde of minum stowe;

76 swa feor swa ðær fram Beatrican min gesiho;
77 ac me ne ofðuhte ðæs, forðæm hire ansyn
78 ne com to me ðurh ænigne middel gemænsum.

91 Þus ic bidde; and heo, swa feor
92 swa heo ðuhte, hyre bleo onwrah and on me locode;
93 ða heo gewende eft to ðam ecan wellan.

97 ðe me hider asende, fleog ðurh ðisne wyrtgeard mid ðinum gesihðum;
98 forðæm ðe ðu hine geseo, ðonne bið ðin gesihð gegearwod
99 ðe sel mæg gestigan ðurh ðone godcundan leoman.

106 ac cwyð on ðam geðance, ða hwile ðe heo æteowed bið:
107 ‘Drihten min Hælend Crist, soð God,
108 wæs ðin ansyn ðus gefeaxod?’;

112 "Sunu ðære gife, ðeos glædnes beoð",
113 ongan he, "ne bið ðe cuð,
114 gif ðu ðine eagan symle her niðer healdeð;

127 swa ðæt sibsum gylde fyr
128 on ðam midle weox brihtre, and on ælce healfe
129 ða leg byð dimre gelice;

133 Ic geseah ðær hi ða plegan and ða songas
